<p><strong>Troll Knight's Sword</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Colossal Swords" href="/Colossal+Swords" target="">Colossal Sword</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The&nbsp;<strong>Troll Knight's Sword</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength">Strength</a>,&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity">Dexterity</a>,&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Intelligence" href="/Intelligence">Intellect</a>&nbsp;and is a good&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;Int/Str Builds.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Greatsword embedded with a blue glintstone.<br>Weapon of the trolls in service to the royal family of Caria. </em></p> 
 <p><em>Called into service when the Queen invoked an oath they swore, <br>the trolls are treated as true knights of Caria, and fight arm in arm with their human comrades.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Troll Knight's Sword in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Troll Knight's Sword weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Randomly dropped by the Troll Knight in&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Caria Manor" href="/Caria+Manor">Caria Manor</a>&nbsp;[<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=2908&amp;lat=-106.15&amp;lng=58.5&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=2908&amp;lat=-106.15&amp;lng=58.5&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>]. <a class="wiki_link" title="Video Location" href="https://youtu.be/neQ-5QWwtI0?t=1470">Video Location</a></li> 
 <li>The two Spectral Troll Knights leading up to <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring The Four Belfries" href="/The+Four+Belfries">The Four Belfries</a>&nbsp;can also drop this item</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Troll Knight's Sword Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Troll's Roar" href="/Troll's+Roar" target="">Troll's Roar</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li>Cannot be enchanted with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells">Magic</a> nor boosted by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables">Consumables</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Troll Knight's Sword</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon's moveset is shared with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Zweihander" href="/Zweihander">Zweihander</a></li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;200</li> 
 <li>Base drop rate is 8% (at 100 Discovery)</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Troll Knight's Sword</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Troll Knight's Sword Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Troll Knight's Sword Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a>.</p> 
<p>This upgrade cannot be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;or boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
